  "title": "Posterior abdominal wall vessels",
  "body_html": "<b>Abdominal aorta</b> <br /><ul><li>Commences at vertebral level T12 </li><li>Ends by bifurcating into right and left common iliac arteries at L4. Anteriorly this corresponds to a point approximately 2cm below the umbilicus just left of the midline.</li></ul><br /><b>Abdominal aorta branches</b><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Branch position</th><th>Type</th><th>Branches</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Anterior</td><td>3 single anterior visceral branches (unpaired)</td><td>coeliac trunk<br />superior mesenteric<br />inferior mesenteric</td></tr><tr><td>Lateral</td><td>3 lateral visceral branches (paired)</td><td>suprarenal<br />renal<br />gonadal</td></tr><tr><td>Lateral</td><td>5 wall branches (paired)</td><td>inferior phrenic and lumbar (but names not required)</td></tr><tr><td>Terminal</td><td>3 branches</td><td>Left common iliac (main branch)<br />Right common iliac (main branch)<br />Median sacral</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br />Level of selected branches/landmarks:<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid2\" ><thead><tr><th><b>Branch of aorta</b></th><th><b>Vertebral Level</b></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Coeliac trunk</td><td>T12</td></tr><tr><td>Superior mesenteric</td><td>L1</td></tr><tr><td>Renal arteries</td><td>L1/2</td></tr><tr><td>Testicular or ovarian arteries</td><td>L2</td></tr><tr><td>Inferior mesenteric artery</td><td>L3</td></tr><tr><td>Bifurcation of the abdominal aorta</td><td>L4</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><br /><b>IVC</b> <br /><ul><li>Commences at vertebral level T8 </li><li>Ends by bifurcating below the aorta at L5 level. </li></ul><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/fti223b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/fti223.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'>Diagram illustrating the abdominal aorta & IVC</div><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb139b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb139.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/diaphragm'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb139b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'>Diagram illustrating the abdominal aorta branches</div><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb140b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb140.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/diaphragm'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_FRCEMtutor/swb140b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><div class='imagetext'>Diagram illustrating the diaphragmatic openin